======================================================================
PART 6: THE 5-CYCLE DENSITY CONJECTURE
======================================================================

CONJECTURE: For any tournament T on n vertices:
  #(5-cycles) / #(3-cycles) ≥ (n-4)(n-5) / (20·1)
  i.e., 5-cycles grow faster than 3-cycles with n

Expected ratio in random tournament:
  E[#5-cyc] / E[#3-cyc] = C(n,5)·3!/(5·2^5) / (C(n,3)/4)
                        = C(n,5)·6/(5·32) / (C(n,3)/4)
                        = 4·C(n,5)·6 / (5·32·C(n,3))
                        = 24·C(n,5) / (160·C(n,3))
                        = 3·C(n,5) / (20·C(n,3))
                        = 3·(n-3)(n-4) / (20·10)

Observed 5-cycle/3-cycle ratio from random sampling:
  n= 5: avg 3-cyc=     2.6, avg 5-cyc=     0.0, ratio= 0.008, f₅=0.0076, (3+2f₅)²=9.09 ≥n ✓
